<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Ann Shia | UX Portfolio</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Manrope:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap');

    :root {
      --primary: #FF6B6B;
      --secondary: #4ECDC4;
      --dark: #2D3436;
      --light: #F8F9FA;
      --gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), var(--secondary));
    }

    body {
      font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
      background-color: var(--light);
      color: var(--dark);
      line-height: 1.6;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .cursor {
      width: 20px;
      height: 20px;
      border: 2px solid var(--primary);
      border-radius: 50%;
      position: fixed;
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 999;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    .cursor-follow {
      width: 8px;
      height: 8px;
      background: var(--primary);
      border-radius: 50%;
      position: fixed;
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 999;
      transition: transform 0.1s ease;
    }

    .progress-bar {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 4px;
      background: var(--gradient);
      transform-origin: 0%;
      z-index: 1000;
    }

    nav {
      padding: 2rem 5%;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      position: fixed;
      width: 100%;
      top: 0;
      background: rgba(248, 249, 250, 0.9);
      backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
      z-index: 100;
    }

    .logo {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      background: var(--gradient);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .logo:hover {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    .nav-links a {
      margin-left: 2rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--dark);
      text-decoration: none;
      position: relative;
    }

    #content {
      padding: 8rem 5% 4rem;
    }

    .section-heading {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      background: var(--gradient);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(30px);
      animation: fadeIn 1.2s ease forwards;
    }

    .content-section {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .content-left {
      flex: 1 1 40%;
      padding-right: 2rem;
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateX(-30px);
      animation: fadeInLeft 1.2s ease forwards;
    }

    .content-right {
      flex: 2 1 60%;
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateX(30px);
      animation: fadeInRight 1.2s ease forwards;
    }

    .content-image {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .content-right p {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    footer {
      background: var(--dark);
      color: var(--light);
      padding: 2rem 5%;
    }

    .footer-content {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .footer-column h4 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--secondary);
    }

    .footer-column a {
      color: var(--light);
      text-decoration: none;
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
      opacity: 0.8;
      transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    }

    .footer-column a:hover {
      opacity: 1;
    }

    /* Keyframe Animations */
    @keyframes fadeIn {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(30px);
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
      }
    }

    @keyframes fadeInLeft {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-30px);
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
      }
    }

    @keyframes fadeInRight {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(30px);
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="cursor"></div>
  <div class="cursor-follow"></div>
  <div class="progress-bar"></div>

  <nav>
    <a href="/" class="logo">Ann Shia</a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="#content">Content</a>
      <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
      <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section id="content">
    <h1 class="section-heading">About My Work</h1>

    <div class="content-section">
      <div class="content-left">
        <img src="./images/about.webp" alt="Work Image" class="content-image">
      </div>
      <div class="content-right">
        <p>As a UX designer, my focus is on crafting digital experiences that seamlessly blend functionality with visual appeal. My projects are designed to address real-world challenges by creating intuitive interfaces that enhance both user satisfaction and business outcomes. Whether it's designing a responsive website, improving accessibility for a broader audience, or reimagining the user journey for a mobile app, I strive to deliver solutions that leave a lasting impact.</p>

<p>My design philosophy is deeply rooted in understanding the user's needs. Through comprehensive user research, I uncover insights that guide the creative process and ensure every design decision is purposeful. I specialize in translating complex ideas into simple, elegant solutions that resonate with users and drive engagement. By integrating feedback at every stage, I ensure that the end product not only meets but exceeds expectations.</p>

<p>With a strong foundation in prototyping, wireframing, and user testing, I aim to create interfaces that are not only functional but also delightful to interact with. Iâ€™m passionate about responsive design, ensuring that my projects look and perform beautifully on all devices. From brainstorming innovative ideas to delivering polished designs, I bring creativity, strategy, and a user-first mindset to every project.</p>

<p>Take a look at my portfolio to explore how these principles come to life across various projects. Whether it's a sleek e-commerce platform, a user-friendly educational app, or a comprehensive design system, each project reflects my dedication to excellence and my passion for creating meaningful digital experiences.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="footer-content">
      <div class="footer-column">
        <h4>About Me</h4>
        <p>I'm a UX designer passionate about creating meaningful, user-centered digital experiences that make an impact.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-column">
        <h4>Connect</h4>
        <a href="#">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="#">GitHub</a>
        <a href="#">Email</a>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-column">
        <h4>Quick Links</h4>
        <a href="#content">About</a>
        <a href="#projects">Projects</a>
        <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const cursor = document.querySelector('.cursor');
    const cursorFollow = document.querySelector('.cursor-follow');

    document.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
      cursor.style.transform = `translate(${e.clientX - 10}px, ${e.clientY - 10}px)`;
      cursorFollow.style.transform = `translate(${e.clientX - 4}px, ${e.clientY - 4}px)`;
    });

    const progressBar = document.querySelector('.progress-bar');
    window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
      const scroll = window.scrollY;
      const maxScroll = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight;
      const progress = (scroll / maxScroll) * 100;
      progressBar.style.width = `${progress}%`;
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>





